Superannuation Benefit Defined Benefit Payments Amount
This is the value, during the relevant period, for benefit payments made to the member of a defined benefit Registrable Superannuation Entity or sub-fund.
Includes insurance claim benefits or proceeds first credited to members' accounts and subsequently disbursed along with members' benefits to the member or beneficiary.
Superannuation Contribution Transaction Count

This is the number, during the relevant period, of contribution transactions that represent an instance of a contribution in respect of a single member or an instance of a contribution in respect of a defined benefit pool in which a group of members has an interest.
Superannuation Fund Details MySuper Product Lifecycle Stage Change Status Code
This indicates how the MySuper product or lifecycle stage, or its reported information, has changed since the previous report.

The valid enumerated values are: Existing = where any information about an existing MySuper product or lifecycle stage has changed. Unchanged = where all information reported remains unchanged from the previous submission. Ceased = where the product or lifecycle stage is no longer offered to members and the value of assets in that product or lifecycle stage is nil. New = where the MySuper product or lifecycle stage was not previously reported. Not applicable = where the MySuper product has a single diversified investment strategy.
Superannuation Fund Details Registration End Date
The date that the sub-fund, MySuper product, select investment option or lifecycle stage ceases to be effective.
Superannuation Fund Details Registration Start Date
The date that the sub-fund, MySuper product, select investment option or lifecycle stage becomes effective.
Superannuation Fund Details Select Investment Option Identifier
This is the unique identifier of the select investment option, as determined by the Registrable Superannuation Entity (RSE) licensee.
Superannuation Fund Details Select Investment Option Name Text
This is the name of the select investment option.
Superannuation Fund Details Select Investment Option Status Code
This indicates how the select investment option reported information has changed since the previous report.

The valid enumerated values are: Existing = where any information about an existing select investment option has changed. Unchanged = where all information reported remains unchanged from the previous submission. Ceased = where the select investment option is no longer offered to members and the value of assets in that select investment option is nil. No longer select investment option = where the select investment option no longer meets the definition of a select investment option. Returning = where the select investment option previously met the definition and has been reported in a prior period. New = where the select investment option was not previously reported.
Superannuation Fund Details Sub Fund Change Status Code
This indicates how the sub-fund, or its reported information, has changed since the previous report.

The valid enumerated values are: Existing = where any information about an existing sub-fund has changed. Unchanged = where all information reported remains unchanged from the previous submission. Ceased = where the RSE or sub-fund is no longer offered to members and the value of assets in that RSE or sub-fund is nil. New = where the sub-fund was not previously reported.
Superannuation Regulatory Information Membership Profile Gender Code
This is the classification, as at the relevant date, of allowable gender of a member in the product.

The valid enumerated values are: Female = Where women are the only determinant for membership in a lifecycle stage Male = Where men are the only determinant for membership in a lifecycle stage. Intersex or Indeterminate = Where intersex or indeterminate gender is the only determinant for membership in a lifecycle stage. Any = Where gender is not a determinant for membership in a lifecycle stage.
Superannuation Regulatory Information Registrable Superannuation Entity Licensee Ownership Code
This indicates, as at the relevant date, the Registrable Superannuation Entity (RSE) licensee ownership type.

The valid enumerated values are: Financial services corporation ownership = where the owner of the RSE licensee is a financial services corporation, i.e. the owner is a legal entity created for the purpose of producing financial goods and services for the market, that may be a source of profit or other financial gain to its owner(s) and it is collectively owned by shareholders who have the authority to appoint directors responsible for its general management. Excludes: a financial services corporation that is the principal employer-sponsor of all RSEs within the RSE licensee's business operations. Employer sponsor (non-public sector) ownership = where the owner of the RSE licensee is the principal employer-sponsor of an RSE within the RSE licensee's business operations. Include: where the RSE licensee is owned by employees of the employer-sponsor. Exclude: where the employer-sponsor is a public sector organisation. Public sector organisation ownership = where the owner of the RSE licensee is an organisation within the government sector or a resident corporation and quasi-corporation controlled by the general government sector. Include: where the public sector organisation is the principal employer-sponsor of an RSE within the RSE licensee's business operations. Nominating organisation ownership = where the owner of the RSE licensee is an employee association or employer association that represents the membership / employers of the RSEs within the RSE licensee's business operations. Include: where the RSE licensee is owned by directors representing the membership / employers of the RSEs within the RSE licensee's business operations. Public company ownership = where the owner of the RSE licensee is a public company. Excludes: a public company that is a financial services corporation, a public company that is the principal employer-sponsor of an RSE. Other ownership type = where the owner of the RSE licensee is not categorised elsewhere.
Superannuation Regulatory Information Sub Fund Existence Indicator
This indicates whether the defined benefit Registrable Superannuation Entity (RSE) has at least one sub-fund.
A choice of TRUE/FALSE values. true = the Registrable Superannuation Entity (RSE) has at least one sub-fund. false = the RSE has no sub-funds.
